article.headline: The Citadel 65, Western Carolina 60
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) -- Warren McLendon scored 18 points and pulled down 16 rebounds to lead The Citadel over Western Carolina 65-60 on Tuesday night. McLendon made 7-of-21 shots, while Donny McLendon scored 15 points and Kevin Hammack added 10 points and four assists for the Bulldogs (7-2, 1-0 Southern Conference). The Catamounts (5-8, 0-1) were led by Antonio Russell, who scored 16 points. Trey Hopkins added 12 points, and David Berghoefer and Corey Muirhead had 8 each. The Citadel took a 35-28 halftime lead, but Western Carolina came back to within four with 9:33 to play. The Catamounts used a 14-2 run and cold shooting from the Bulldogs, who went six minutes without a point, to close the gap to four at 50-46. Hammack made two free throws to give The Citadel the five-point win.
